'''Gustaf Johan Lagerbielke, 11th Baron Lagerbielke''' ({{IPA|sv|ˈɡɵ̂sːtav ˈlɑ̂ːgɛ(r)ˌbjɛlkɛ}}; born 10 April 2000) is a Swedish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Primeira Liga]] side [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|500894}}</ref>

== Early life ==
Gustaf grew up as a [[Swedish nobility|nobleman]] in [[Djursholm]] outside Stockholm. His mother is Katarina Waldenström, an entrepreneur, and his father is Johan Lagerbjelke, the 8th Count Lagerbjelke, a public speaker and negotiation expert.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-transfer-news/celtic-transfer-targetgustaf-lagerbielke-title-30659104 |title=Celtic transfer target Gustaf Lagerbielke has a title of BARON and is No.254 in line to the Swedish throne |date=8 August 2023 |publisher=Daily Record |access-date=8 August 2023}}</ref> His grandfather Jan Waldenström played for [[IF Elfsborg]]. His stepfather is Swedish industrialist Per-Olof Söderberg, who bears no relation to former national team coach [[Tommy Söderberg]].{{citation needed|date=April 2024}}

== Club career ==
Lagerbielke played for [[AIK Fotboll|AIK]], [[Sollentuna FK]], [[Västerås SK Fotboll|Västerås SK]], [[IF Elfsborg]] and [[Degerfors IF]] in Sweden. In August 2023, he joined Scottish club [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]], by signing a contract until 2028.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gp.se/boras/elfsborgs-gustaf-lagerbielke-klar-for-celtic-.d3c5fef9-725c-4f19-be0b-bc0ffd21952f |title=Elfsborgs Gustaf Lagerbielke klar för Celtic |website=gp.se |language=sv |date=16 August 2023 }}</ref>

Lagerbielke made his [[Old Firm]] Derby debut on 3 September 2023, notably winning a goal-cancelling foul to help Celtic to a 1–0 win away to [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sverige - Island - Matchfakta - Svensk fotboll |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-island-landskamper-herr-senior/5387000/ |access-date=13 January 2023 |website=www.svenskfotboll.se |language=sv |archive-date=12 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230112201020/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-island-landskamper-herr-senior/5387000/ |url-status=dead}}</ref> Later that year, on 13 December, he scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal, securing a 2–1 victory over [[Feyenoord]], to seal his club's first win in 15 matches in that competition, and first home win in ten years.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2023/12/13/celtic-vs-feyenoord-live-score-updates-champions-league/ |title=Gustaf Lagerbielke earns Celtic first Champions League home win in a decade – reaction |author=PA Sport |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=13 December 2023 }}</ref>

On 27 August 2024, Lagerbielke joined [[FC Twente|Twente]] in the Netherlands on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Twente|url=https://fctwente.nl/nieuws/gustaf-lagerbielke-naar-fc-twente|title=Gustaf Lagerbielke naar FC Twente|trans-title=Gustaf Lagerbielke to FC Twente|date=27 August 2024|access-date=27 August 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

On 8 July 2025, Lagerbielke departed Celtic to join [[Primeira Liga]] side [[S.C. Braga]] on a permanent deal.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2025-07-08 |title=Gustaf Lagerbielke leaves Celtic |url=https://www.celticfc.com/news/2025/july/08/gustaf-lagerbielke-leaves-celtic/ |access-date=2025-07-22 |website=Celtic FC |language=en}}</ref>

== International career ==
[[File:Gustaf Lagerbielke (Sweden vs Moldova, 12 October 2023).jpg|thumb|258x258px|Lagerbielke with [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] in 2023]]
Lagerbielke made his debut for [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden's national team]] on 12 January 2023 in a friendly match against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-island-landskamper-herr-senior/5387000/ |title=Sverige 2–1 Island |website=svenskfotboll.se |language=sv |date=12 January 2023 |access-date=16 January 2023 |archive-date=12 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230112201020/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-island-landskamper-herr-senior/5387000/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> On 12 October 2023, he scored his first international goal in a 3–1 victory over [[Moldova national football team|Moldova]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2023/10/herr-swe-mda/ |title=Svensk seger i genrepet mot Belgien |website=svenskfotboll.se |language=sv |date=12 October 2023 }}</ref>  He scored a goal in Swedens winning game in the play off finals for the [[2026 World Cup]] against Poland on 31 March 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c8dl97er10lt|title=Sweden 3-2 Poland: Viktor Gyokeres winner fires Graham Potter's side to World Cup|website=BBC Sport|accessdate=31 March 2026}}</ref>

On 12 May 2026, Lagerbielke was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

